The paper deals with finding local Nash equilibria in two-player zero-sum games, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses the use of a differential structure to construct an algorithm, which suggests a connection to control theory (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper involves the training of a generative adversarial network (GAN), which is a popular topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the convergence properties of the algorithm, which suggests a connection to numerical analysis (cs.NE).
